\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {B.12}{\ignorespaces  Posterior distributions of the model parameters for the S~CrA streamer. The panels show, from top left to bottom right, the MCMC-points peak solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_grid_peak_cornerplot_A.}), the MCMC-points posterior median solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_grid_median_cornerplot_A.}), the MCMC-global peak solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_shell_map_cornerplot_A.}), and the MCMC-global posterior median solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_shell_median_cornerplot_A.}). One-dimensional histograms and two-dimensional joint distributions illustrate the parameter constraints and correlations, demonstrating the increased stability and reduced degeneracy achieved when the full PPV information is incorporated through the shell-based likelihood. In each panel, the solid blue lines mark the locations of the posterior median and peak values, while the dashed black lines indicate the $\pm 34\%$ confidence intervals derived from the marginalized posterior distributions. }}{74}{figure.caption.60}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:SCrA_results_cornerplot_A.}{{B.12}{74}{Posterior distributions of the model parameters for the S~CrA streamer. The panels show, from top left to bottom right, the MCMC-points peak solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_grid_peak_cornerplot_A.}), the MCMC-points posterior median solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_grid_median_cornerplot_A.}), the MCMC-global peak solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_shell_map_cornerplot_A.}), and the MCMC-global posterior median solution (\ref {fig:SCrA_mcmc_shell_median_cornerplot_A.}). One-dimensional histograms and two-dimensional joint distributions illustrate the parameter constraints and correlations, demonstrating the increased stability and reduced degeneracy achieved when the full PPV information is incorporated through the shell-based likelihood. In each panel, the solid blue lines mark the locations of the posterior median and peak values, while the dashed black lines indicate the $\pm 34\%$ confidence intervals derived from the marginalized posterior distributions}{figure.caption.60}{}}
